main event: A civilian observer reported seeing one round object, about the size of a nickel, moving west at a low rate of speed in St Cloud, Minnesota on July 23, 1955.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for seven to eight minutes., The object crossed a major portion of the sky during the observation period., The object was highly suggestive of aircraft., A Northwestern flight had recently departed Minneapolis for Fargo around the time of the sighting., No photographs were included with the report.
